description:
Google's line of products and services to clients never stops growing. Strategic Partner Development Managers have the rare opportunity to build a long-lasting relationship with our top partners. You cultivate these existing partnerships to make sure they can take full advantage of Google's ever-growing suite of offerings. You possess strong relationship-building skills and are apt to see mutually beneficial opportunities with partners in order to best represent our users, products and programs.

As a Strategic Partner Development Manager, you will empower and enable the organization’s project teams by understanding their mission, identifying partners, initiating relationships, negotiating agreements, and serving as a strategic resource to advance the research work and product launches. You will work on early stage product development alongside Research Scientists and Product Managers to realize product visions through external partner development.

Google’s Global Partnerships team powers extraordinary user experiences through meaningful partnerships. We build relationships that solve users’ needs, advance our partners’ goals, and further Google’s mission. Our team provides solutions for a range of partners — from helping publishers and developers grow their businesses through monetization solutions, to helping our long-term partners anticipate and navigate change in a way that delivers economic and reputational value. We build and distribute Google products through partnerships across a multitude of product areas, including Search, Assistant, Geo, News, Travel, and more. We collaborate across Google, ensuring a coordinated approach when engaging with our most complex and strategic partners.

qualifications:
Minimum qualifications:

  • Bachelor's degree or equivalent practical experience.
  • 5 years of experience in a partner-facing role at a technology company or start-up.

Preferred qualifications:

  • Experience in technology, business development, or other entrepreneurial environment.
  • Experience in partner management, product management, or product marketing in an Internet or technology environment.
  • Experience in negotiating complex, one-of-a-kind agreements.
  • Educational background or work experience in science.
  • Ability to concurrently manage multiple time-sensitive projects/agreements in a fast-paced environment with minimal direction.
responsibilities:
• Identify and lead exploratory discussions with partner prospects.
  • Develop and create strategy documents and partner communication collateral.
  • Invest in understanding the complex technical areas of the Research and Machine Intelligence organization.
  • Negotiate strategic product partnerships agreements.
title: Strategic Partner Development Manager, Global Product Partnerships
